// Operating system consist two types, i) shell, ii) Kernel.
// Kernel is the program interface to interact with hardware.
// Shell is Graphical User Interface ( GUI ) to interact with operating system, intact that is hardware.

// We use many types of Unix systems such as LINUX, and Mac OS also use unix OS.
// Windows use DOS Operating system.

// Why we use Command line ?
// Command line gives faster access to interact with hardware of system and gives more control than GUI.

// To create new directory ( folder ), open hyper and give this
mkdir music

// To list all files inside specific path. (This command displays, hidden files also)
ls -a
